---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Methodology — The Great Stabbing">
  <section class="px-6 py-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto prose">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Methodology</h1>
    <p class="text-stone">
      Full methodology document lives in the repo at
      <a href="https://github.com/victor-velazquez-ai/great-stabbing/blob/main/docs/methodology.md">
        docs/methodology.md</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone mt-4">
      Headline rules:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-stone space-y-2 mt-2">
      <li>Show only what the official source publishes. No imputation, ever.</li>
      <li>The foreign-background variable is shown only where the source publishes it
        (DE BKA, DK Statbank, AT BMI, occasional SE BRÅ). Always with absolute counts
        AND rates per 100k of the relevant population group.</li>
      <li>News-extracted incidents are illustrative pins, never aggregated into rates.</li>
      <li>Suspect descriptions are verbatim quotes from sources. Nationality fields are
        filled only when an article explicitly states them.</li>
      <li>No names of victims or suspects appear on the map.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
